Score: 5
<p>In light of the spread of COVID-19 in New York City, A.R.T./New York has moved all of its programming online. This includes workshops, roundtables, and all other in-person meetings. A.R.T./New York Staff will also be working remotely during this time, and will be available via email and phone during our normal office hours. We prioritize the health and safety of our community, and we will keep you up to date with any more developments surrounding the coronavirus.</p>

<p><span><strong>If you have been furloughed but would like to continue receiving communications from A.R.T./New York</strong>, contact Membership Coordinator Jeannely Lopez at <a href="mailto:jlopez@art-newyork.org">jlopez@art-newyork.org</a> to update your staff profile contact information.</span></p>

<p>Thank you, and if&#160;you have any questions, please do not hesitate to reach out to us.</p>

